Recommended Visit Frequency by Customer

Each customer's optimal visit interval is calculated from their sell-through velocity: Visit Every = 83 hats (40% of display) / daily hats sold. Visit before the display drops below 60% full to place a reorder and keep it above the 50% floor.

Visit Frequency vs. Average Order Value

Bubble size = net revenue. Customers in the upper-left sell fast and order big (highest priority). Customers in the lower-right sell slowly and order small (lowest priority).

Display Depletion Curves by Segment

Shows how many days it takes each segment to sell through a full 208-hat display. The orange zone (60%) is when you should visit. The red zone (50%) is the hard floor - the display needs restocking immediately.
